1>Go to script runner
2>Click on UI Fragments
3>Click on create UI Fragments
4>Now select Install web resource
5>Provide the name
6>select the context -> customerportal, jira.view.issue
7>create a key example issue-view-colour (key should be different/unique)
8>style.css
9>click on update

Create a resource: test-resources/red-text.css.
a.	Create the test-resources folder within the web-resources/com.onresolve.jira.groovy.groovyrunner directory.
b.	Create a file named red-text.css.
c.	Edit that file in a text editor.
d.	Enter the following contents:

Note : go to jira select the button -> right click inspect->now check the id number
/* To do transition*/
a/action_id_11{
	background: grey;
	boarder-radius: 10px;
	color: #ffffff;
}

/* In Progress transition*/
a/action_id_21{
	background: blue;
	boarder-radius: 10px;
	color: #ffffff;
}

/* Done transition*/
a/action_id_31{
	background: green;
	boarder-radius: 10px;
	color: #ffffff;
}
e.	Save the file
